<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-69-0459 </DOCNO><TEXT>Methods by which the topology of magnetic field lines can be describedboth globally and locally are reviewed. The importance of topologicalconstraints in the calculation of magnetostatic equilibria is demonstrated.The rms braiding of two curves due to random boundary motions is considered.35 references.</TEXT></DOC>